## Lakebase registry backend: end-to-end wiring

Context: OntoBricks now supports persisting the domain registry on
Databricks Lakebase (Postgres) in addition to the existing Unity
Catalog Volume backend. The choice is admin-selectable in
**Settings → Registry / Registry Location**, defaults to ``volume``,
and binary artefacts (``documents/``, ``*.lbug.tar.gz``) keep living
on the Volume regardless of which backend is active. Authentication
is fully app-managed: the Databricks Apps runtime injects
``PGHOST``/``PGPORT``/``PGDATABASE``/``PGUSER`` and ``LakebaseAuth``
mints OAuth tokens automatically — no user secret. Both Provisioned
and Autoscaling Lakebase tiers are supported, with cold-start retry
on ``SQLSTATE 57P03``.

This entry covers the final ribbon of the migration: API route, DAB
overlay targets, app.yaml env wiring, contract test suite, and docs.
The earlier per-service refactor (RegistryService / PermissionService
/ BuildScheduler / GlobalConfigService now delegate JSON-shaped
operations to a ``RegistryStore`` ABC), the cache-key tagging, the
admin UI chooser, and the migration helper itself were landed in
preceding sessions on this branch.

Changes:

1. src/api/routers/internal/settings.py
   New ``POST /settings/registry/migrate-to-lakebase`` route (admin
   only) that drives the one-shot Volume → Lakebase copy.
2. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   New ``migrate_to_lakebase_result`` orchestrator: builds the source
   ``VolumeRegistryStore`` and destination ``LakebaseRegistryStore``,
   delegates to ``migrate_volume_to_lakebase``, and returns a
   single-line summary plus the structured ``MigrationReport`` for
   the admin UI.
3. databricks.yml
   Added ``registry_backend``/``lakebase_database``/
   ``lakebase_instance``/``lakebase_schema`` bundle variables and
   two opt-in target overlays — ``dev-lakebase`` and ``prod-lakebase``
   — that attach a ``database`` Apps resource to both
   ``ontobricks_app`` and ``mcp_ontobricks_app``. Default ``dev``/
   ``prod`` targets stay Volume-only so existing deployments are
   unchanged.
4. app.yaml
   Documented that the database resource binding makes the
   Apps runtime auto-inject ``PGHOST``/``PGPORT``/``PGDATABASE``/
   ``PGUSER`` (no ``valueFrom`` mapping needed) and added
   ``LAKEBASE_SCHEMA`` env var (default ``ontobricks_registry``).
5. src/mcp-server/app.yaml
   Same Lakebase comment + ``LAKEBASE_SCHEMA`` for the MCP server.
6. tests/test_registry_store.py
   New contract test suite: ``build_store`` factory (Volume default,
   unknown-backend fallback, lazy-import safety for Lakebase),
   :class:`RegistryStore` behavioural contract (idempotent
   initialize, missing-row no-raise, write/read round-trip,
   permissions/global-config/history shapes), Volume cache key
   backend-tag assertion, and migration round-trip + idempotency
   driven by an in-memory fake store.
7. tests/test_registry.py
   Brought existing tests in line with the store-routed paths:
   ``RegistryCfg.as_dict`` now exposes ``backend``/``lakebase_schema``
   defaults, ``_make_settings`` seeds them, ``_make_svc`` pre-resolves
   the store-side domain folder, and the delete/write/initialize
   tests assert against the new (path, dict, ``overwrite=True``)
   call shape.
8. tests/test_permissions.py
   Reworked domain-permission tests to mock
   ``PermissionService._store_for`` instead of the now-deleted
   ``_new_uc``/``_domain_permissions_path`` internals.
9. README.md
   Added Lakebase prerequisite + ``uv sync --extra lakebase`` note,
   plus the ``-t dev-lakebase`` / ``-t prod-lakebase`` deploy
   instructions.
10. .env.example
    Documented ``REGISTRY_BACKEND``, ``LAKEBASE_SCHEMA``, and the
    auto-injected ``PG*`` variables (with a no-hardcoded-password
    note since the password is a runtime OAuth token).
11. docs/architecture.md
    Replaced the "Unity Catalog Versioning" section with a broader
    "Registry Storage Backends" section that lists both backends,
    the Postgres table layout, the auth model, and the binaries-stay-
    on-Volume invariant.

