================================================================
Lakebase migration: surface the actual error in admin UI
================================================================

Reported issue
--------------
The admin clicked "Migrate to Lakebase" and got back the toast
"Error: Migration completed with errors — domains=0, versions=0,
 permission_sets=0, schedules=0, history=0, global_config=no;
 errors=1." with no indication of *which* error. The structured
``report.errors`` array was returned in the JSON payload but never
displayed.

Fixes
-----
1. src/back/objects/registry/store/migration.py
   ``summarize()`` now appends the first error message to the
   summary string (and ``(+N more)`` when there are several), so
   the toast notification immediately tells the admin what failed
   (most commonly the destination ``initialize`` step: connection
   refused, missing DB, permission denied on CREATE SCHEMA, missing
   ``pgcrypto``, etc.).
2. src/front/static/registry/js/registry.js
   The migrate handler now logs the full ``data.report`` object
   to the browser console (collapsed group) and prints every entry
   from ``report.errors`` as ``console.warn``, so operators can
   inspect every error, not just the first.
3. tests/test_registry_store.py
   Strengthened ``test_summarize_flags_errors`` and added
   ``test_summarize_flags_multiple_errors`` covering the new
   first-error suffix and the ``+N more`` accumulator.

Modified files:
- src/back/objects/registry/store/migration.py
- src/front/static/registry/js/registry.js
- tests/test_registry_store.py

